  "objective": "Build a counter that cycles 0→1→2→0",
  "description": "Not all counters are powers of 2! A mod-3 counter counts 0, 1, 2, then wraps back to 0. This requires custom next-state logic — you can't just chain flip-flops. BCD counters (mod-10) in clocks and calculators use the same principle.",
